correctness.rationale: Extraction is largely incorrect and not schema-/article-aligned. Key issues: (1) ALD method: Set to TALD, but article describes atmospheric, manifold-head ALD separated by shielding gas (spatial ALD); should be SALD. (2) Schema violation: plasmaPower is present as null, but the field is optional and, if present, must be an object; remove or populate correctly. (3) Pressure: Value 101325 with unit MilliM_HG (mmHg) is wrong (≈133 atm). The article states atmospheric pressure; should be ~760 mmHg. (4) Numerous fabricated/unsupported parameters: growth per cycle, number of cycles, film thickness (120 nm), saturation, nucleation period, dosing/purge times, and all flow rates are not reported anywhere. (5) Supercycle design and subcycle sequence including N co-reactant are not described in the paper. (6) Material properties: Optical properties (refractive index, absorption coefficient, UV-Vis method) are not reported; the 3.4 eV band gap is a general statement, not a measured value. Uniformity, conformality, elemental concentrations/atomic ratio (XPS), roughness (AFM value), and film density (unit/value error: 5.6 g/dm³ is incorrect and no density method/data given) are unsupported. (7) Electrical properties: Resistivity ~1000 Ω·m for 100 °C sample is traceable; mobility 0.2 cm²/V·s is plausible for ≤150 °C samples after dark anneal. However, carrier density is wrong in units/magnitude: the article reports up to 1×10^15 cm⁻³ (≈1×10^21 m⁻³), not 1×10^15 m⁻³. (8) Device properties (TFT mobility, Vth, SS, on/off, device structure) are not in the article. (9) Multiple processes: The paper reports deposits across several temperatures (100–300 °C); only one process (100 °C) is extracted; additional processes are missing. Overall, many values are invented, not traceable, or unit-inconsistent. Properties to correct/review: aldSystem.aldMethod, processParameters.plasmaPower, processParameters.pressure, all thicknessControl fields, dosing/purge/flow entries, supercycleDesign, optical/uniformity/conformality/composition/roughness/filmDensity/deviceProperties, and electrical carrier density units/value; add separate processes for other deposition temperatures if extracted.

completeness.rationale: The extraction is largely non-traceable to the article and has schema issues, so completeness is very poor. Key problems: (1) Many values are fabricated and not reported in the article: dosingTime, purgeTime, flowRates, growthPerCycle, numberofCycles, filmThickness (120 nm), saturation, nucleationPeriod, supercycleDesign sequence, optical refractiveIndex/absorption/band gap and UV-Vis method, XPS elemental concentrations and atomic ratios, film density (XRR), uniformity/conformality metrics, and all TFT device properties. These are not mentioned and violate traceability. (2) ALD method is incorrect: the article reports atmospheric ALD with a manifold head and shielding gas (spatial ALD), but the extraction lists TALD; it should be SALD. (3) Pressure is wrong/inconsistent: value 101325 with unit MilliM_HG is not traceable; atmospheric pressure should be ~760 mmHg; the article only states atmospheric pressure. (4) Schema compliance issues: plasmaPower is set to null (type mismatch; property is optional and should be omitted if not used). (5) Partial/cited values are misused or overspecified: band gap 3.4 eV is a generic ZnO value from the introduction, not a measurement; resistivity of ~1000 Ω·m for the 100 °C ZnO:N sample is traceable, but specific mobility (0.2 cm^2/V·s) and carrier density (1×10^15 cm^-3) are ranges, not exact sample values. (6) The article describes multiple depositions across temperatures (100–300 °C) with distinct resulting properties; only a single process at 100 °C is extracted—multiple processes should be represented. Properties to add/review: correct aldMethod to SALD; represent separate processes for 100, 150, 200, and 300 °C; include only traceable parameters (substrate, temperature range, atmospheric pressure, precursors/co-reactants, carrier/purge gas, manifold/shielding delivery); remove or mark unknown for dosing/purge/flows/GPC/cycles/film thickness unless cited; remove unreported optical, XPS/composition, density, uniformity/conformality, and all device properties; correct pressure unit/value; omit plasmaPower if not used; include post-anneal treatments if schema allows or note them qualitatively in otherAspects.
